
[1]chasideans

   ASSIDE'ANS or CHASIDE'ANS, [Heb. pious.]

   A sect of Jews who resorted to Mattathias to fight for the laws of
   their God and the liberties of their country. They were men of great
   zeal, and observed the traditions of the elders. From these sprung the
   Pharisees and Essenes.
